====Exceptions====
* [[Re-Raising Exceptions|https://www.techbeamers.com/use-try-except-python/#raising-exceptions-in-Python]]

```
def main():
    Do this
    Do that
    try:
        age = int(input("Please enter your age: "))
        if age < 0:
            raise ValueError("%d is not a valid age. Age must be positive or zero.")
    except ValueError as err:
        print("You entered incorrect age input: %s" % err)
    else:
        print("I see that you are %d years old." % age)
```

